I've become a convert to the whole ebook thing recently, but only in a limited capacity. I still like having a paper book for most things I read like history, the real value comes from replacing all those Technical books that you buy.

There is a small subset of all the technical books I have that I really want a paper copy of. Stuff like my Operating System books that you cannot get anymore. But in general technical books date so quickly that if you're looking at something more that a year and a half old it's pretty much useless. 

Looking at my current bookshelf, there is probably half or more books that are severly outdated and aren't any use in their current form. What I'd be better off doing is to grab an ebook reader (or just use my Mac) and 
